      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">What is Kundli Milan?</h2>
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
        Kundli Milan is the process of comparing two birth charts to assess compatibility between potential marriage partners. The classical method uses 36 Gunas (qualities) to evaluate various aspects of compatibility. Each match is scored; a higher score suggests smoother compatibility and better prospects for a harmonious marriage.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
        However, it's important to understand that a lower Guna score does not mean a relationship will fail — it simply indicates areas that may need more attention and understanding between the partners.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">The 36 Gunas and Their Meaning</h2>
      
      <div class="my-8">
        <img
          src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1578662996442-48f60103fc96?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
